RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EFFECTIVE GIG was off alertly, controlled early pace from the inside, was asked for more passing three-eighths markers and shook well clear and never menaced after that while ridden out. CORAZON DE LUCIA was bumped by inside rival in opening strides, closest in pursuit in two path, lost contact with winner early on the final backstretch and held the place. DANNY MICHAEL reserved from the inside, hugged the rail throughout and proved best of the rest. HUMBLEBUMBLEFUMBLE broke out and bumped LUKE'S PLACE then brushed hind quarters of HUMBLEBUMLEFUMBLE, chased three wide early, remained off the rail and weakened. LUKE'S PLACE was bumped by inside rival then squeezed in a slow start, settled off the pace and off the rail, chased four then three wide to the stretch and failed to make any late impact.

ENTRY.NAME: Danny Michael
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, inside, hugged rail, no late threat

ENTRY.NAME: Effective Gig
ENTRY.COMMENT: off alertly, pace, shook clear past 3/8, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Luke's Place
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, squeezed start, off rail, 3wide, 2wide, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERSEVERANCE was well placed off the leader for a half mile, rallied two wide to the stretch then pushed past late. FORT YORK set all the pace for six furlongs, responded to mid stretch but could not stall the winner. INDIANERA was rank and bore out five wide on the first turn, chased after being corrected, was asked for more two wide on the far turn and closed the gap to the line. ZOE'S PAPA CEE was carried out six deep on the first turn by INDIANERA, settled on the backstretch then second time then rallied three wide to the stretch and also closed ground late. MOUNT PELLIAR settled mid pace for a half mile then saved ground to the stretch but lacked the needed late response. SYNC had no speed and was not a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled mid pack, saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Perseverance
ENTRY.COMMENT: well placed, asked 2wide, steady stretch run, driving

ENTRY.NAME: Fort York
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, responded far turn, caught, 2d best

ENTRY.NAME: Indianera
ENTRY.COMMENT: rank, bore out 1st turn, chased pace, asked 2wide, closed gap

ENTRY.NAME: Zoe's Papa Cee
ENTRY.COMMENT: carried 6wide 1st turn, settled, roused 3wide, closed ground
